00:50.365 --> 00:52.365
You look nervous.

00:52.367 --> 00:54.316
Me? No.

00:54.318 --> 00:56.169
- Yeah.
- Why?

00:56.171 --> 00:57.587
I've never been to City Hall.

00:57.589 --> 00:58.921
It's called Village Hall.

00:58.923 --> 01:01.874
- What?
- Evan, relax.

01:01.876 --> 01:03.543
You're gonna be great.

01:03.545 --> 01:05.093
- I know.
- Mr. and Mrs. Lawson.

01:05.096 --> 01:06.546
- Ms. Ballard.
- Hi.

01:06.548 --> 01:08.831
What brings the two of you
here to Village Hall?

01:08.833 --> 01:10.433
All of our other neighbors
have agreed to allow Hankmed

01:10.435 --> 01:11.684
to continue to operate

01:11.686 --> 01:13.502
- out of Shadow Pond.
- Right.

01:13.504 --> 01:14.637
So I'm submitting a signed petition

01:14.639 --> 01:16.806
to ask for a zoning waiver.

01:16.808 --> 01:18.808
I hope you won't take this
too personally or anything.

01:18.810 --> 01:20.977
[Laughs]
Of course not.

01:20.979 --> 01:22.678
In fact, after your lovely party

01:22.680 --> 01:25.181
I started thinking maybe
I should support Hankmed.

01:25.183 --> 01:28.284
Oh! Well... I...

01:28.286 --> 01:29.685
I don't know what to say.

01:29.687 --> 01:32.405
But I also thought that before
I signed anything,

01:32.407 --> 01:34.207
I should do my due diligence.

01:34.209 --> 01:35.958
And that's when I discovered

01:35.960 --> 01:38.578
that Hankmed doesn't have
a valid business license.

01:38.580 --> 01:40.213
So even if you wanted to get

01:40.215 --> 01:41.664
on tonight's agenda, you couldn't,

01:41.666 --> 01:43.666
because you're not a business.

01:49.890 --> 01:51.974
What do you mean
we're not a valid business?

01:51.976 --> 01:53.643
I know. It's crazy.

01:53.645 --> 01:55.211
I forgot to check one little box

01:55.213 --> 01:56.345
when I applied for our original license.

01:56.347 --> 01:58.881
Like, one box, Henry! A little one.

01:58.883 --> 02:00.216
The woman is like a psycho.

02:00.218 --> 02:01.484
She's out to get me or something.

02:01.486 --> 02:02.602
Okay, I'm... I'm sorry.

02:02.604 --> 02:03.903
So, we've never been licensed?

02:03.905 --> 02:05.071
I've already fixed it.

02:05.073 --> 02:08.024
We just have to shut down for,
like, 72 hours.

02:08.026 --> 02:09.390
- Why?
- That's how long

02:09.393 --> 02:11.527
the business license will take
to get processed.

02:11.529 --> 02:13.946
- Three days?
- I prefer 72 hours.

02:13.948 --> 02:15.531
Luckily, we have a light schedule.

02:15.533 --> 02:17.399
Yeah, we also won't have
Divya and Jeremiah.

02:17.401 --> 02:19.619
They'll both be in Savannah.
Which is why Paige

02:19.621 --> 02:22.421
has already rescheduled
all non-emergent appointments.

02:22.423 --> 02:23.623
If there is an emergency,

02:23.625 --> 02:26.242
one of the on call doctors
can handle it.

02:26.244 --> 02:28.261
For you, I've booked a massage,

02:28.263 --> 02:31.747
a yoga class, and a golf lesson.

02:31.749 --> 02:35.101
I'm sorry, massages, yoga,
and golf for three days?

02:35.103 --> 02:38.521
72 hours.

02:38.523 --> 02:39.755
Henry, you need to relax.

02:39.757 --> 02:41.358
I've spent the last six months relaxing.

02:41.359 --> 02:42.859
I want to be working.

02:42.861 --> 02:44.927
- You're also a little tense.
- I'm not tense!

02:44.929 --> 02:48.147
- I'm angry!
- All right.

02:48.149 --> 02:51.567
In that case, I'll cancel the golf.

02:51.569 --> 02:55.121
The massage is at 2:00. Yoga's at 4:00.

