03:10.671 --> 03:13.789
What's Dmitry doing
with Boris's Porsche?

03:13.791 --> 03:16.425
I don't know.
Maybe he's getting it serviced?

03:16.427 --> 03:19.061
What I do know is Dmitry
is still out of town.

03:20.731 --> 03:22.565
Maybe I should take a trip.

03:22.567 --> 03:26.402
That's a great idea.
I'm so happy you said that.

03:26.404 --> 03:28.437
Where would you go?
You could go to Miami,

03:28.439 --> 03:30.323
- or the Bahamas, or...
- Budapest.

03:30.325 --> 03:32.658
Yeah, that would have been my next idea.

03:32.660 --> 03:34.744
Oh.

03:34.746 --> 03:35.811
Seriously?

03:35.813 --> 03:37.146
Milos is still eager to talk,

03:37.148 --> 03:39.832
but insists that we meet in person.

03:39.834 --> 03:42.001
It made me wonder if he knows
something about Boris's death.

03:42.003 --> 03:44.820
So, what, you'd tell Milos
your suspicions about Dmitry?

03:44.822 --> 03:46.622
I need to get to know him first.

03:46.624 --> 03:49.008
Well, here's a crazy idea.

03:49.010 --> 03:50.509
Why don't we just go together?

03:50.511 --> 03:52.094
No, no. You need to stay here

03:52.096 --> 03:54.463
and take care of our non-business.

03:54.465 --> 03:56.766
Hey, our non-business
is sending you to Europe.

03:56.768 --> 03:58.935
Show a little gratitude.

04:01.855 --> 04:04.840
[Upbeat music]

04:04.842 --> 04:05.342
d

04:17.519 --> 04:19.822
[Phone ringing]

04:19.824 --> 04:21.824
Excuse me.

04:23.860 --> 04:27.747
Yes, thank you for calling me back.

04:27.749 --> 04:33.386
I have an appointment to check
my HCG levels on Monday.

04:33.388 --> 04:36.639
Monday. At 4:30.

04:36.641 --> 04:38.874
I'd like to see if
I could come in early.

04:42.712 --> 04:44.931
I see.

04:44.933 --> 04:47.350
No, no. No, thank you anyway.

04:48.435 --> 04:50.436
[Grunts]

04:51.888 --> 04:53.773
Uh, after we check in,
I thought that we'd...

04:53.775 --> 04:55.741
I've rearranged our itinerary.

05:01.064 --> 05:03.666
Jeremiah, what's the rush?
We're here for two days.

05:03.668 --> 05:05.067
I've decided to go back tonight.

05:05.069 --> 05:06.735
Well, hello, Hankmed!

05:06.737 --> 05:08.237
There you are!

05:08.239 --> 05:10.756
Welcome to Savannah.

05:10.758 --> 05:13.342
Hi. Mary Kay Higgins.

05:13.344 --> 05:14.910
Director of Symphony Guest Services.

05:14.912 --> 05:16.963
I am so sorry that I missed
y'all at the airport.

05:16.965 --> 05:19.348
I tried to retrieve you two
at the luggage go-round.

05:19.350 --> 05:20.800
We didn't check in any bags.

05:20.802 --> 05:22.351
- I'm leaving tonight.
- Uh-huh.

05:22.353 --> 05:23.585
But we are so looking forward

05:23.587 --> 05:25.888
- to our tour of Savannah General.
- Well, terrific,

05:25.890 --> 05:27.923
'cause your rooms here
aren't quite ready yet,

05:27.925 --> 05:29.775
but that will give me plenty
of time to make it up to you.

05:29.777 --> 05:31.927
I'm parked right over here.

05:31.929 --> 05:35.648
Now, the health and wellness
fair starts at 3:00.

05:35.650 --> 05:37.817
So, I'm first gonna show you
our fair city,

05:37.819 --> 05:39.819
and then I thought y'all
might like to see

05:39.821 --> 05:41.404
Savannah's sand Gnats.

05:41.406 --> 05:43.122
I think that Dr. Sacani
is in a hurry, so...

05:43.124 --> 05:45.607
Ms. Higgins, I would love
to see your sand Gnats.

05:49.279 --> 05:50.612
- Thank you.
- You're welcome.

05:50.614 --> 05:52.281
Don't forget, folks, today is the first

05:52.283 --> 05:55.451
of two games against
the Augusta Greenjackets.

05:55.453 --> 05:57.119
[Pipe organ playing]

05:57.121 --> 05:59.555
How do you know about the sand Gnats?

05:59.557 --> 06:02.174
They're a single "A" farm team.

06:02.176 --> 06:05.127
Well, I have never been
to a baseball game before.

06:05.129 --> 06:07.796
I had no idea that you were such
a big fan of base...

06:07.798 --> 06:11.901
Ball? That was right down Broadway!

06:11.903 --> 06:15.154
All: Let's go, Moe! Let's go, Moe!

06:15.156 --> 06:16.405
Let's go, Moe!

06:16.407 --> 06:18.407
Now up to bat, Moe Gilley.

06:20.160 --> 06:21.777
[Crowd reacts]
And Franklin beats him

06:21.779 --> 06:23.662
on a high outside pitch.
He's pitching him outside.

06:23.664 --> 06:24.980
He should go to the opposite field.

06:24.982 --> 06:27.316
They're shading him to pull left.

06:27.318 --> 06:29.919
- Pull left why, Jeremiah?
- Moe Gilley.

06:29.921 --> 06:32.838
Back up to the plate.

06:32.840 --> 06:34.590
[Crack]
[Crowd reacts]

06:34.592 --> 06:36.842
Oh, he shatters his bat!

06:36.844 --> 06:39.128
Oh, so you make an out

06:39.130 --> 06:41.380
- if you break your bat.
- No.

06:41.382 --> 06:43.332
Then why is he going back to the bunker?

06:43.334 --> 06:45.968
- The dugout.
- Oh, like cricket.

06:45.970 --> 06:48.804
Nothing like cricket.

06:48.806 --> 06:49.972
Why is he talking to that player?

06:49.974 --> 06:51.507
He's not a coach.

06:51.509 --> 06:54.527
- Is that even allowed.
- Yes.

06:54.529 --> 06:57.613
Because he's no longer
in the bunker... dugout.

06:57.615 --> 06:58.898
He's in the ready area.

06:58.900 --> 07:00.232
How much longer is this gonna go on?

07:00.234 --> 07:03.069
I know. This game does seem
to be rather long.

07:03.071 --> 07:05.621
No, I was talking about your questions.

07:05.623 --> 07:08.124
And Gilley struggling
a little bit, with two strikes

07:08.126 --> 07:12.078
and no runners on base.
[Cheering]

07:12.080 --> 07:13.529
[Crack]
And he races a single

07:13.531 --> 07:16.415
out to right field.
[Cheering]

07:16.417 --> 07:18.367
Ah, right field. Right advice.

07:18.369 --> 07:21.203
Tripp Doby up to bat,
one runner on base.

07:21.205 --> 07:22.721
Tripp is batting a .187,

07:22.723 --> 07:25.707
three RBIs, and one homerun this season.

07:25.709 --> 07:28.310
[Crack]
And he rips one to right field!

07:28.312 --> 07:32.064
Going... and it's gone!

07:32.066 --> 07:33.382
[Crowd reacts]
And takes a fall

07:33.384 --> 07:36.152
before he gets to first base.

07:36.154 --> 07:38.720
[Cheering]
He... he's back up.

07:43.527 --> 07:46.078
He's rounding third...
and he falls again!

07:46.080 --> 07:48.447
There must be something wrong.

